HEADWORD: crackerberry
<hw>crackerberry</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a creeping red-berried
perennial herb (<spn>Cornus canadensis</spn>) distinguished by clustered
leaf whorls at tips of shoots; Greenland to Alaska.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bunchberry, dwarf cornel, pudding berry, <spn>Cornus
canadensis</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

